CHIKUNGUNYA (37): PAKISTAN
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: 29 Sep 2017
Source: Pakistan Today [edited]
https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2017/09/29/karachi-witnesses-154-chikungunya-cases-in-september/


At least 241 suspected cases have been reported throughout Sindh province from 1 Sep 2017 to date; out of these 241 cases, 154 emerged from Karachi alone.

Sindh Health Department released a report which stated that a total of 4329 chikungunya suspected cases surfaced in the province, out of which 3462 were from Karachi, while the rest of the cases surfaced in Tharparkar/Mithi, Sanghar and Umerkot.

Out of a total of 3462 in Karachi, 1740 cases were reported in District Malir, 156 in District Central, 180 in District South, 1210 in District West, 165 in District East, and 11 in District Korangi.

Chikungunya is transmitted to humans by infected mosquitoes. The major symptoms include high fever, joint pain, joint swelling, rash, headache, muscle pain, nausea and fatigue. Chikungunya is rarely fatal, and the death rate of the disease-affected people is less than one percent.

